cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on analyzing the memory-centric characteristics of the SPEC CPU2017 benchmark suite on x86_64 ISA, which falls under the domain of computer architecture. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper provides insights into the performance of the benchmark suite in terms of memory capacity consumption, memory bandwidth utilization, and working set sizes. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper uses hardware performance counters and operating system-based tools to measure the performance of the benchmark suite, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper uses dynamic binary instrumentation to analyze the benchmark suite, which falls under the domain of software engineering. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper performs instruction distribution analysis of the benchmark suite and compares it with the previous version (SPEC CPU2006), which falls under the domain of programming languages.
